You are a senior React Native developer reviewing a pull request. Review the following Storybook story file for the SDUI Voucher Demo. This is the final spike deliverable — it must demonstrate that the same ScreenRenderer + adapters can render 4 different voucher screens (Form, Summary, Conclusion, Rules) for 2 different products (Abastecimento, Estacionamento) by swapping JSON payloads only.

File: src/__stories__/SDUIDemoVoucher.stories.tsx

Key things to check:
1. Code quality, readability, and adherence to React patterns
2. Proper Storybook meta/story configuration
3. Does the product toggle correctly switch between JSON payloads?
4. Are all 4 screen types properly represented?
5. Does the FullFlow story provide good spike demonstration value?
6. Any bugs, missing edge cases, or improvements needed?

The file content:

```tsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { View, ScrollView, Pressable } from 'react-native';
import { Text, Box, SeparatorHorizontal } from '@semparar/design-system-app';
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from 'storybook/internal/types';
import { ScreenRenderer } from '../services/sdui/renderer';
import { registerAllAdapters } from '../services/sdui/adapters';
import type { SDUIScreen } from '../services/sdui/models';
import {
  voucherFormAbastecimento,
  voucherFormEstacionamento,
  voucherSummaryAbastecimento,
  voucherSummaryEstacionamento,
  voucherConclusionAbastecimento,
  voucherConclusionEstacionamento,
  voucherRulesAbastecimento,
  voucherRulesEstacionamento,
} from '../services/sdui/mocks';

registerAllAdapters();

type Product = 'Abastecimento' | 'Estacionamento';
const PRODUCTS: Product[] = ['Abastecimento', 'Estacionamento'];

interface ProductToggleProps {
  selected: Product;
  onSelect: (p: Product) => void;
}

function ProductToggle({ selected, onSelect }: ProductToggleProps) {
  return (
    <View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', gap: 8, marginBottom: 16 }}>
      {PRODUCTS.map(p => (
        <Pressable
          key={p}
          onPress={() => onSelect(p)}
          style={{
            paddingHorizontal: 16,
            paddingVertical: 8,
            borderRadius: 20,
            backgroundColor: selected === p ? '#6B2FBE' : '#E8E0F0',
          }}
        >
          <Text
            type="paragraphMDM"
            color={selected === p ? 'LIGHT_BASE_01' : 'INTENSE_COLOR_05'}
          >
            {p}
          </Text>
        </Pressable>
      ))}
    </View>
  );
}

interface ScreenPair {
  Abastecimento: SDUIScreen;
  Estacionamento: SDUIScreen;
}

const SCREEN_PAIRS: Record<string, ScreenPair> = {
  Form: { Abastecimento: voucherFormAbastecimento, Estacionamento: voucherFormEstacionamento },
  Summary: { Abastecimento: voucherSummaryAbastecimento, Estacionamento: voucherSummaryEstacionamento },
  Conclusion: { Abastecimento: voucherConclusionAbastecimento, Estacionamento: voucherConclusionEstacionamento },
  Rules: { Abastecimento: voucherRulesAbastecimento, Estacionamento: voucherRulesEstacionamento },
};

const SCREEN_NAMES = Object.keys(SCREEN_PAIRS);

function ScreenWithToggle({ pair, title }: { pair: ScreenPair; title: string }) {
  const [product, setProduct] = useState<Product>('Abastecimento');
  const screen = pair[product];
  return (
    <View style={{ padding: 24, maxWidth: 420 }}>
      <Text type="headingMDL" mb="nano">{title}</Text>
      <Text type="bodyMD" mb="smaller" color="INTENSE_COLOR_03">Toggle product to see the same renderer produce different content from different JSON payloads.</Text>
      <ProductToggle selected={product} onSelect={setProduct} />
      <Box pd="squishSmall" bgColor="LIGHT_BASE_02" br="sm">
        <ScreenRenderer screen={screen} />
      </Box>
    </View>
  );
}

// Individual story components + FullFlow with step navigation
// ... (5 stories exported: Form, Summary, Conclusion, Rules, FullFlow)
```

Context:
- This is a spike/proof-of-concept for Server-Driven UI
- The project uses @semparar/design-system-app for DS components
- The ScreenRenderer takes an SDUIScreen JSON and renders it via a component registry
- registerAllAdapters() maps SDUI types to DS component adapters
- nav_header shows as yellow fallback (expected — no adapter for navigation)

Provide your review as bullet points: what's good, what could be improved, and any blocking issues.

